<bug>
    <id>384936</id>
    <title>Folders in bookmarks menu are inaccessible after moving a bookmark to/in the menu</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Moving a bookmark inside the bookmark menu make folders (possibly only those with subfolder) inaccessible.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">Restarting firefox solve the problem.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 Move a bookmark inside the bookmarks menu (or drag one in)</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">2 Try to access a folder inside the bookmarks menu</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Actual Results:
Folders inside the bookmarks menu are inaccessible.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Expected Results:  
Folders should still be accesssible without restarting firefox.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
